During a press briefing, White House Press Secretary Jen Psaki introduced Secretary of Veterans Affairs Denis McDonough as a special guest. Secretary McDonough spoke about the importance of the American Rescue Plan in providing support to the VA to provide quality care to veterans during the pandemic. He highlighted the impact of the pandemic on veterans, including job loss and infection rates among veterans. He also discussed the efforts of the VA to provide vaccinations and routine care through telehealth. Secretary McDonough emphasized the need for additional funding from the American Rescue Plan to meet the increased demand for care and address the backlog of disability claims. He also mentioned the importance of the VA in helping veterans cope with the economic impact of the pandemic. Following Secretary McDonough's remarks, Psaki took questions on various topics, including vaccine distribution, veteran healthcare, and the response to the January 6th attack on the Capitol.